84","/letters/letter_84",{"title":1026,"_path":1027},"Letter 85","/letters/letter_85",{"title":1029,"_path":1030},"Letter 86","/letters/letter_86",{"title":1032,"_path":1033},"Letter 87","/letters/letter_87",{"title":1035,"_path":1036},"Letter 88","/letters/letter_88",{"title":1038,"_path":1039},"Letter 89","/letters/letter_89",{"title":777,"_path":1041},"/letters/letter_example","i-heroicons-envelope",{"title":1044,"_path":1045,"children":1046},"Sayings","/sayings",[1047],{"title":1048,"_path":1049},"Sayings of Imam Ali","/sayings/sayings",{"_path":26,"_dir":1051,"_draft":1052,"_partial":1052,"_locale":1053,"title":25,"description":1054,"body":1055,"_type":1325,"_id":1326,"_source":1327,"_file":1328,"_extension":1329},"sermons",false,"",null,{"type":1056,"children":1057,"toc":1317},"root",[1058,1070,1077,1086,1094,1099,1107,1119,1127,1132,1140,1145,1153,1161,1167,1175,1180,1188,1194,1202,1207,1215,1221,1229,1234,1242,1250,1256,1261,1266,1271,1276,1281],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1061,"children":1062},"element","p",{},[1063],{"type":1059,"tag":1064,"props":1065,"children":1066},"em",{},[1067],{"type":1068,"value":1069},"text","Delivered on return from Siffin",{"type":1059,"tag":1071,"props":1072,"children":1074},"h2",{"id":1073},"arabia-before-proclamation-of-prophethood",[1075],{"type":1068,"value":1076},"Arabia before proclamation of Prophethood",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1079,"children":1080},"blockquote",{},[1081],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1082,"children":1083},{},[1084],{"type":1068,"value":1085},"ومن خطبة له ) عليه السلام (بعد انصرافه من صفين",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1087,"children":1088},{},[1089],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1090,"children":1091},{},[1092],{"type":1068,"value":1093},"وفيها حال الناس قبل البعثة وصفة آل النبي ثمّ صفة قوم آخرين:",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1095,"children":1096},{},[1097],{"type":1068,"value":1098},"I praise Allah seeking completion of His Blessing, submitting to His\nGlory and expecting safety from committing His sins. I invoke His help\nbeing in need of His Sufficiency (of protection). He whom He guides does\nnot go astray, He with whom He is hostile gets no protection. He whom He\nsupports does not remain needy. Praise is most weighty of all that is\nweighed and the most valuable of all that is treasured.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1100,"children":1101},{},[1102],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1103,"children":1104},{},[1105],{"type":1068,"value":1106},"أحْمَدُهُ اسْتِتْماماً لِنِعْمَتِهِ، وَاسْتِسْلاَماً لِعِزَّتِهِ، واسْتِعْصَاماً مِنْ مَعْصِيَتِهِ، وَأَسْتَعِينُهُ\nفَاقَةً إِلى كِفَايَتِهِ، إِنَّهُ لاَ يَضِلُّ مَنْ هَدَاهُ، وَلا يَئِلُ مَنْ عَادَاهُ، وَلا يَفْتَقِرُ مَنْ\nكَفَاهُ; فَإِنَّهُ أَرْجَحُ ما وُزِنَ، وَأَفْضَلُ مَا خُزِنَ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1108,"children":1109},{},[1110,1112,1117],{"type":1068,"value":1111},"I stand witness that there is no god but Allah the One. He has no like.\nMy testimony has been tested in its frankness, and its essence is our\nbelief. We shall cling to it for ever till we live and shall store it\nfor facing the tribulations that overtake us because it is the\nfoundation stone of Belief ",{"type":1059,"tag":1064,"props":1113,"children":1114},{},[1115],{"type":1068,"value":1116},"(iman)",{"type":1068,"value":1118}," and the first step towards good\nactions and Divine pleasure. It is the means to keep Satan away.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1120,"children":1121},{},[1122],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1123,"children":1124},{},[1125],{"type":1068,"value":1126},"وَأَشْهَدُ أَنْ لاَ إِلهَ إِلاَّ اللهُ، شَهَادَةً مُمْتَحَناً إِخْلاَصُهَا، مُعْتَقَداً مُصَاصُهَا، نَتَمَسَّكُ\nبها أَبَداً ما أَبْقانَا، وَنَدَّخِرُهَا لاِهَاوِيلِ مَا يَلْقَانَا، فَإِنَّها عَزيمَةُ الاْيمَانِ،\nوَفَاتِحَةُ الاْحْسَانِ، وَمَرْضَاةُ الرَّحْمنِ، وَمَدْحَرَةُ الشَّيْطَانِ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1128,"children":1129},{},[1130],{"type":1068,"value":1131},"I also stand witness that Muhammad (S) is His slave and His Prophet.\nAllah sent him with the illustrious religion, effective emblem, written\nBook, effulgent light, sparkling gleam and decisive injunction\nin order to dispel doubts, present clear proofs, administer warning\nthrough signs and to warn of punishments. At that time people had fallen\nin vices whereby the rope of religion had been broken, the pillars of\nbelief had been shaken, principles had been sacrileged, system had\nbecome topsy turvy, openings were narrow, passage was dark, guidance was\nunknown and darkness prevailed.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1133,"children":1134},{},[1135],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1136,"children":1137},{},[1138],{"type":1068,"value":1139},"وَأَشْهَدُ أَنَّ مُحَمَّداً عَبْدُهُ وَرَسُولُهُ، أرْسَلَهُ بِالدِّينِ المشْهُورِ، وَالعَلَمِ المأْثُورِ،\nوَالكِتَابِ المسْطُورِ، وَالنُّورِ السَّاطِعِ، وَالضِّيَاءِ اللاَّمِعِ، وَالاَمْرِ الصَّادِعِ، إزَاحَةً\nلِلشُّبُهَاتِ، وَاحْتِجَاجاً بِالبَيِّنَاتِ، وَتَحْذِيراً بِالايَاتِ، وَتَخْويفاً بِالمَثُلاَتِ، وَالنَّاسُ\nفي فِتَن انْجَذَمَ فِيها حَبْلُ الدِّينِ، وَتَزَعْزَعَتْ سَوَارِي اليَقِينِ، وَاخْتَلَفَ النَّجْرُ، وَتَشَتَّتَ\nالاْمْرُ، وَضَاقَ الْـمَخْرَجُ، وَعَمِيَ المَصْدَرُ، فَالهُدَى خَامِلٌ، واَلعَمَى شَامِلٌ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1141,"children":1142},{},[1143],{"type":1068,"value":1144},"Allah was being disobeyed, Satan was given support and Belief had been\nforsaken. As a result the pillars of religion fell down, its traces\ncould not be discerned, its passages had been destroyed and its streets\nhad fallen into decay. People obeyed Satan and treaded his paths. They\nsought water from his watering places. Through them Satan's emblems got\nflying and his standard was raised in vices which trampled the people\nunder their hoofs, and treaded upon them with their feet. The vices\nstood on their toes (in full stature) and the people immersed in them\nwere strayed, perplexed, ignorant and seduced as though in a good\nhouse with bad neighbours. Instead of sleep they had\nwakefulness and for antimony they had tears in the eyes. They were in a\nland where the learned were in bridle (keeping their mouths shut) while\nthe ignorant were honoured.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1146,"children":1147},{},[1148],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1149,"children":1150},{},[1151],{"type":1068,"value":1152},"عُصِيَ الرَّحْمنُ، وَنُصِرَ الشَّيْطَانُ، وَخُذِلَ الاِْيمَانُ، فَانْهَارَتْ دَعَائِمُهُ، وَتَنكَّرَتْ مَعَالِمُهُ،\nوَدَرَسَتْ سُبُلُهُ، وَعَفَتْ شُرُكُهُ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1154,"children":1155},{},[1156],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1157,"children":1158},{},[1159],{"type":1068,"value":1160},"أَطَاعُوا الشَّيْطَانَ فَسَلَكُوا مَسَالِكَهُ، وَوَرَدُوا مَنَاهِلَهُ، بِهِمْ سَارَتْ أَعْلامُهُ، وَقَامَ\nلِوَاؤُهُ، في فِتَن دَاسَتْهُمْ بِأَخْفَافِهَا، وَوَطِئَتْهُمْ بأَظْلاَفِهَا وَقَامَتْ عَلَى سَنَابِكِهَا، فَهُمْ\nفِيهَا تَائِهُونَ حَائِرونَ جَاهِلُونَ مَفْتُونُونَ، في خَيْرِ دَار، وَشَرِّ جِيرَان، نَوْمُهُمْ سُهُودٌ،\nوَكُحْلُهُمْ دُمُوعٌ، بأَرْض عَالِمُها مُلْجَمٌ، وَجَاهِلُها مُكْرَمٌ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1071,"props":1162,"children":1164},{"id":1163},"in-the-same-sermon-amir-al-muminin-referred-to-al-an-nabi-the-household-of-the-holy-prophet-as-under",[1165],{"type":1068,"value":1166},"In the same sermon Amir al-mu'minin referred to Al an-Nabi (the Household of the Holy Prophet) as under",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1168,"children":1169},{},[1170],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1171,"children":1172},{},[1173],{"type":1068,"value":1174},"ومنها: ويعني آل النبي ( صلى الله عليه وآله وسلم)",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1176,"children":1177},{},[1178],{"type":1068,"value":1179},"They are the trustees of His secrets, shelter for His affairs, source of\nknowledge about Him, centre of His wisdom, valleys for His books and\nmountains of His religion. With them Allah straightened the bend of\nreligion's back and removed the trembling of its limbs.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1181,"children":1182},{},[1183],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1184,"children":1185},{},[1186],{"type":1068,"value":1187},"هُمْ مَوْضِعُ سِرِّهِ، وَلَجَأُ أَمْرِهِ، وَعَيْبَةُ عِلْمِهِ، وَمَوْئِلُ حُكْمِهِ، وَكُهُوفُ كُتُبِهِ، وَجِبَالُ\nدِينِه، بِهِمْ أَقَامَ انْحِناءَ ظَهْرِهِ، وَأذْهَبَ ارْتِعَادَ فَرَائِصِهِ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1071,"props":1189,"children":1191},{"id":1190},"in-the-same-sermon-he-spoke-about-the-hypocrites",[1192],{"type":1068,"value":1193},"In the same Sermon he spoke about the hypocrites",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1195,"children":1196},{},[1197],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1198,"children":1199},{},[1200],{"type":1068,"value":1201},"منها: يعني بها قوماً آخرين",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1203,"children":1204},{},[1205],{"type":1068,"value":1206},"They sowed vices, watered them with deception and harvested destruction.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1208,"children":1209},{},[1210],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1211,"children":1212},{},[1213],{"type":1068,"value":1214},"زَرَعُوا الفُجُورَ، وَسَقَوْهُ الغُرُورَ، وَحَصَدُوا الثُّبُورَ ،",{"type":1059,"tag":1071,"props":1216,"children":1218},{"id":1217},"ali-muhammad",[1219],{"type":1068,"value":1220},"Ali Muhammad",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1222,"children":1223},{},[1224],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1225,"children":1226},{},[1227],{"type":1068,"value":1228},"آل محمد (عليه السلام)",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1230,"children":1231},{},[1232],{"type":1068,"value":1233},"None in the Islamic community can be taken at par with the\nProgeny of the Prophet (Ali Muhammad). One who was under their\nobligation cannot be matched with them. They are the foundation of\nreligion and pillar of Belief. The forward runner has to turn back to\nthem while the follower has to overtake them. They possess the chief\ncharacteristics for vicegerency. In their favour exists the will and\nsuccession (of the Prophet). This is the time when right has returned to\nits owner and diverted to its centre of return.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1235,"children":1236},{},[1237],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1238,"children":1239},{},[1240],{"type":1068,"value":1241},"لا يُقَاسُ بِآلِ مُحَمَّد (عليهم السلام) مِنْ هذِهِ الاُمَّةِ أَحَدٌ، وَلا يُسَوَّى بِهِمْ مَنْ جَرَتْ\nنِعْمَتُهُمْ عَلَيْهِ أبَداً.",{"type":1059,"tag":1078,"props":1243,"children":1244},{},[1245],{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1246,"children":1247},{},[1248],{"type":1068,"value":1249},"هُمْ أَسَاسُ الدِّينِ، وَعِمَادُ اليَقِينِ، إِلَيْهمْ يَفِيءُ الغَالي، وَبِهِمْ يَلْحَقُ التَّالي، وَلَهُمْ\nخَصَائِصُ حَقِّ الوِلايَةِ، وَفِيهِمُ الوَصِيَّةُ وَالوِرَاثَةُ، الاْنَ إِذْ رَجَعَ الحَقُّ إِلَى أَهْلِهِ،\nوَنُقِلَ إِلَى مُنْتَقَلِهِ.",{"type":1059,"tag":1071,"props":1251,"children":1253},{"id":1252},"alternative-sources-for-sermon-2",[1254],{"type":1068,"value":1255},"Alternative Sources for Sermon 2",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1257,"children":1258},{},[1259],{"type":1068,"value":1260},"(1) Ibn Qutaybah, 'Uyun, I, 326;",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1262,"children":1263},{},[1264],{"type":1068,"value":1265},"(2) al-Tabari, al-Mustarshid, p. 73;",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1267,"children":1268},{},[1269],{"type":1068,"value":1270},"(3) Ibn 'Abd Rabbih, al-'Iqd, III, 112;",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1272,"children":1273},{},[1274],{"type":1068,"value":1275},"(4) al-'Amidi, Ghurar, 331, 354;",{"type":1059,"tag":1060,"props":1277,"children":1278},{},[1279],{"type":1068,"value":1280},"(5) Ibn Talhah, Matalib, I.",{"type":1059,"tag":1282,"props":1283,"children":1284},"ul",{},[1285,1291,1296],{"type":1059,"tag":1286,"props":1287,"children":1288},"li",{},[1289],{"type":1068,"value":1290},"The Preserved\nRecord.]",{"type":1059,"tag":1286,"props":1292,"children":1293},{},[1294],{"type":1068,"value":1295},"Good House means\n'Mecca' while the bad neighbours mean the 'Unbelievers of\nQuraysh.']",{"type":1059,"tag":1286,"props":1297,"children":1298},{},[1299,1301,1305,1307,1310,1312,1315],{"type":1068,"value":1300},"About the Progeny\nof the Prophet Amir al-mu'minin has said that no person in the\nworld can be brought at par with them, nor can any one be deemed\ntheir equal in sublimity, because the world is overladen with their\nobligations and has been able to secure eternal blessings only\nthrough their guidance. They are the corner stone and foundation of\nreligion and the sustenance for its life and survival. They are such\nstrong pillars of knowledge and belief that they can turn away the\nstormy flow of doubt and suspicion.]",{"type":1059,"tag":1302,"props":1303,"children":1304},"br",{},[],{"type":1068,"value":1306},"They are such middle course among the paths of excess and\nbackwardness that if some one goes far towards excess and\nexaggeration or falls behind then unless he comes back or steps\nforward to that middle course he cannot be on the path of Islam.\nThey possess all the characteristics which give the superiority in\nthe right for vicegerency and leadership. Consequently, no one else\nin the ummah enjoys the right of patronage and guardianship. That is\nwhy the Prophet declared them his vicegerents and successors. About\nwill and succession the commentator Ibn Abi'l-Hadid Mu`tazili\nwrites that there can be no doubt about the vicegerency of Amir\nal-mu'minin but succession cannot imply succession in position\nalthough the Shi`ite sect has so interpreted it. It rather implies\nsuccession of learning.",{"type":1059,"tag":1302,"props":1308,"children":1309},{},[],{"type":1068,"value":1311},"Now, if according to him succession is taken to imply succession in\nlearning even he does not seem to succeed in achieving his object,\nbecause even by this interpretation the right of succeeding the\nProphet does not devolve on any other person. When it is agreed that\nlearning is the most essential requirement of khilafah (caliphate)\nbecause the most important functions of the Prophet's Caliph\nconsist of dispensation of justice, solving problems of religious\nlaws, clarifying intricacies and administration of religious\npenalties. If these functions are taken away from the Prophet's\ndeputy his position will come down to that of a worldly ruler. He\ncannot be regarded as the pivot of religious authority. Therefore\neither we should keep governmental authority separate from\nProphet's vicegerency or accept the successor of Prophet's\nknowledge to suit that position.",{"type":1059,"tag":1302,"props":1313,"children":1314},{},[],{"type":1068,"value":1316},"The interpretation of Ibn Abi'l-Hadid could be acceptable if Amir\nal-mu'minin had uttered this sentence alone, but observing that it\nwas uttered soon after `Ali's (p.b.u.h.) recognition as Caliph and\njust after it the sentence \"Right has returned to its owner\"\nexists, this interpretation of his seems baseless. Rather, the\nProphet's will cannot imply any other will except that for\nvicegerency and caliphate, and succession would imply not succession\nin property nor in knowledge because this was not an occasion to\nmention it here but it must mean the succession in the right\nleadership which stood proved as from Allah not only on the ground\nof kinship but on the ground of qualities of perfection.",{"title":1053,"searchDepth":1318,"depth":1318,"links":1319},2,[1320,1321,1322,1323,1324],{"id":1073,"depth":1318,"text":1076},{"id":1163,"depth":1318,"text":1166},{"id":1190,"depth":1318,"text":1193},{"id":1217,"depth":1318,"text":1220},{"id":1252,"depth":1318,"text":1255},"markdown","content:2.sermons:2. Sermon_2.md","content","2.sermons/2. Sermon_2.md","md",[1054,1054],1714025123224]